1:48:23.440 --> 1:48:24.720
Don’t ever forget it.

1:48:49.040 --> 1:48:51.600
You know what sound
an offshore boat makes?

1:48:51.680 --> 1:48:52.600
No.

1:49:15.400 --> 1:49:20.000
You never wanted me
to kiss your mouth, Giovanni!

1:49:20.080 --> 1:49:22.920
Well, fine. I’ll kiss it now.

1:49:23.400 --> 1:49:28.960
I’ll bite it with my teeth
like one bites a ripe fruit!

1:49:29.840 --> 1:49:32.040
Giovanni, why won’t you look at me?

1:49:33.080 --> 1:49:37.040
Your terrible eyes,

1:49:37.120 --> 1:49:42.000
so full of anger and contempt,
are closed now!

1:49:42.640 --> 1:49:45.240
Lift up your eyelids, Giovanni!

1:49:45.320 --> 1:49:47.400
Julia, cut!

1:49:48.760 --> 1:49:51.280
-Who said that?
-Me, Capuano.

1:49:52.960 --> 1:49:54.200
Cut, Julia.

1:49:54.280 --> 1:49:57.240
You’ve entered into
the ornamental, zero nuance.

1:49:57.320 --> 1:49:59.520
You’re self-referential,
you’re unraveling.

1:49:59.600 --> 1:50:02.720
One final note, we're tired of your shit.

1:50:08.000 --> 1:50:09.640
Bravo!

1:50:09.720 --> 1:50:11.840
You got the fuck off the stage!

1:50:11.920 --> 1:50:14.200
Now you deserve a round of applause.

1:50:14.280 --> 1:50:18.440
It's what they all wanted,
but they didn’t have the courage.

1:50:22.160 --> 1:50:25.120
Capuano! I’m Fabietto Schisa.

1:50:25.200 --> 1:50:26.800
What the fuck do I care?

1:50:26.880 --> 1:50:30.040
-I’m a huge fan of yours.
-I fucking hate fans.

1:50:30.120 --> 1:50:33.880
I like conflict,
without conflict you don’t progress.

1:50:33.960 --> 1:50:36.880
Without conflict, it’s just sex
and sex is useless.

1:50:38.040 --> 1:50:39.400
Wait!

1:50:39.880 --> 1:50:41.440
You still here?

1:50:42.520 --> 1:50:46.560
-What are you looking at?
-Looking is all I know how to do.

1:50:46.640 --> 1:50:48.760
What d'ya want from me?

1:50:48.840 --> 1:50:51.160
What do I want? Everything!

1:50:51.240 --> 1:50:56.400
That really shocked me, I didn’t know
you could protest at the theater.

1:50:56.480 --> 1:51:00.000
You can’t, but I do
whatever the fuck I want. I’m free.

1:51:00.080 --> 1:51:03.000
-Are you free?
-I’d prefer to answer later.

1:51:04.000 --> 1:51:07.320
-Do you have courage?
-A less difficult question?

1:51:07.960 --> 1:51:11.480
Remember, those without courage
don’t sleep with beautiful women.

1:51:11.960 --> 1:51:13.440
Listen, Capuano…

1:51:14.680 --> 1:51:18.040
Now that my family has disintegrated,
I don’t like life anymore.

1:51:18.760 --> 1:51:21.840
I don’t like it anymore,
I want an imaginary life,

1:51:21.920 --> 1:51:24.240
just like the one I had before.

1:51:24.640 --> 1:51:26.520
I don’t like reality anymore.

1:51:26.600 --> 1:51:28.040
Reality is lousy.

1:51:28.720 --> 1:51:30.600
That’s why I want to make films,

1:51:30.680 --> 1:51:33.520
even though
I’ve only seen three or four.

1:51:35.240 --> 1:51:38.040
Not enough, Schisa. It’s not enough.

1:51:39.320 --> 1:51:43.440
Films…
Everyone wants to make fucking films!

1:51:43.960 --> 1:51:47.240
To make films, you gotta have balls,
do you have balls?

1:51:47.320 --> 1:51:49.040
I rather doubt it.

1:51:49.120 --> 1:51:51.920
So you need pain. You got that?

1:51:52.000 --> 1:51:55.960
Yes, I told you, on that front I’m good.

1:51:56.040 --> 1:51:58.800
What did you tell me? What pain?

1:51:58.880 --> 1:52:02.680
No, you don’t have pain, you have hope.

1:52:02.760 --> 1:52:06.520
With hope you make
comforting films, it’s a trap.

1:52:06.600 --> 1:52:08.960
They left me alone, that’s pain.

1:52:09.040 --> 1:52:12.560
It’s not enough, Schisa! We’re all alone.

1:52:12.640 --> 1:52:16.480
You’re alone? I don’t give a fuck,
because you’re not original.

1:52:17.080 --> 1:52:22.000
Forget pain and think about fun,
that’s how you’ll make films.

1:52:22.080 --> 1:52:26.000
But you gotta have something to say.
You got somethin'?

1:52:26.920 --> 1:52:31.760
Imagination, creativity are myths
that aren’t good for shit.

1:52:32.600 --> 1:52:36.080
I dunno if I have something to say.
How do I know?

1:52:36.160 --> 1:52:37.960
How the fuck do I know!

1:52:38.040 --> 1:52:41.200
I only got four things to say, and you?

1:52:41.880 --> 1:52:46.440
I want to go to Rome to see
if I’m cut out for making films.

1:52:46.520 --> 1:52:49.000
Rome? The great escape…

1:52:49.920 --> 1:52:54.120
Fucking distractions, in the end
you come back to yourself,

1:52:54.200 --> 1:52:58.640
you come back to failure,
everything’s a failure, a pile of shit.

1:52:59.680 --> 1:53:04.040
No one can escape his own failure
and no one gets outta this city.

1:53:04.680 --> 1:53:08.000
Rome…
What the fuck you gonna do in Rome?

1:53:08.600 --> 1:53:11.080
Only assholes go to Rome.

1:53:11.160 --> 1:53:14.400
Do you know how many stories
there are in this city?

1:53:14.480 --> 1:53:16.000
Look!

1:53:34.680 --> 1:53:39.040
Is it possible this city
doesn’t inspire you at all?

1:53:39.680 --> 1:53:42.720
So, you got somethin’ to say?

1:53:42.800 --> 1:53:45.320
Or are you an asshole
like everyone else?

1:53:46.000 --> 1:53:47.800
Got a story to tell?

1:53:48.400 --> 1:53:49.840
Have some guts!

1:53:49.920 --> 1:53:52.480
Got a story to tell or not?

1:53:52.560 --> 1:53:56.040
C’mon, you fool!
Got a story to tell?

1:53:57.880 --> 1:54:00.840
Find the guts to tell it! C’mon!

1:54:01.880 --> 1:54:04.680
-Got a story to tell?
-Yes!

1:54:04.760 --> 1:54:06.200
Then spit it out!

1:54:08.320 --> 1:54:11.200
When my parents died
they didn’t let me see them!

1:54:20.400 --> 1:54:22.560
Don’t come undone, Fabio.

1:54:36.120 --> 1:54:39.360
-Everyone calls me Fabietto.
-Time they start callin’ you Fabio.

1:54:40.800 --> 1:54:41.760
Don’t come undone.

1:54:44.200 --> 1:54:45.440
What does that mean?

1:54:46.240 --> 1:54:48.240
You gotta figure it out yourself.

1:54:49.280 --> 1:54:51.840
You gotta figure it out yourself,
you piece of shit!

1:54:52.280 --> 1:54:53.960
Don’t come undone, Schisa.

1:54:54.480 --> 1:54:57.920
Don’t ever come undone!
You can’t allow that.

1:54:58.000 --> 1:54:59.800
What does that mean? Why?

1:55:01.320 --> 1:55:03.760
Because they didn’t leave you alone.

1:55:06.440 --> 1:55:07.640
No?

1:55:07.720 --> 1:55:08.760
No!

1:55:10.000 --> 1:55:11.840
They abandoned you.

1:55:15.400 --> 1:55:18.320
Listen to me, don’t go to Rome.

1:55:19.240 --> 1:55:21.960
Come see me, I’m always here.

1:55:22.800 --> 1:55:24.960
We’ll make films together!

1:56:07.960 --> 1:56:12.440
<i>You wanted to greet</i>
<i>these marvelous fans personally.</i>

1:56:12.520 --> 1:56:14.600
<i>What did it feel like, Diego?</i>

1:56:14.680 --> 1:56:18.360
<i>The greatest thing in my life.</i>

1:56:21.680 --> 1:56:25.480
<i>The match is over!</i>
<i>Napoli wins the Italian championship!</i>

1:57:01.760 --> 1:57:06.280
<i>An incredibly exciting moment,</i>
<i>Napoli wins the Italian championship!</i>

1:57:08.240 --> 1:57:10.520
<i>It's a thrilling moment…</i>

2:00:24.040 --> 2:00:27.400
-Shall we go to Trastevere?
-I wanna go out to eat.

2:00:27.480 --> 2:00:29.360
-A nice carbonara.
-<i>Cacio e pepe</i>.

2:00:30.640 --> 2:00:33.440
-Excuse me, how much longer to Rome?
-One hour.

